observationText: The SMBCi003-A cell line is a female induced pluripotent stem cell (iPSC) line derived from a 21-year-old Han Chinese patient with neurofibromatosis type 1 carrying the NF1 c.496_497delGT mutation.
The SMBCi003-A cell line exhibited pluripotency markers like NANOG, OCT4, TRA-1-60, TRA-1-81, and alkaline phosphatase activity, and could differentiate into all three germ layers in vitro.
The SMBCi003-A cell line was confirmed to be free of mycoplasma contamination.
